This paper deals with medical imaging tasks and proposes a novel approach for multi-contrast MRI reconstruction. The proposed approach involves dictionary learning, sparse coding, and $k$-space consistency enforcing. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves signal processing and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.IT, cs.MM, and cs.NA.
